T1  - Employee Attitudes as a Function of Age and Length of Service: A Reconceptualization
AU  - Gibson, James L.
AU  - Klein, Stuart M.
Y1  - 1970/12/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254831
DO  - 10.5465/254831
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 411
EP  - 425
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The data reported here suggest: (1) a linear positive relationship between employee satisfaction and age, and (2) a linear negative relationship between employee satisfaction and length of service. The data also indicate that both relationships are asymptotic, thus suggesting limits on increments and decrements in satisfaction as a function of the two explanatory variables. The authors otter explanations for these relationships which have implications for theory, research, and practice.
AB  - The data reported here suggest: (1) a linear positive relationship between employee satisfaction and age, and (2) a linear negative relationship between employee satisfaction and length of service. The data also indicate that both relationships are asymptotic, thus suggesting limits on increments and decrements in satisfaction as a function of the two explanatory variables. The authors otter explanations for these relationships which have implications for theory, research, and practice.
