N2  - This study attempts to analyze the relationship between control, bases of control, and three categories of satisfaction. Data are analyzed by using both group and individual measures. A total of 228 employees of a large insurance company participated in the study. The findings enlarge, extend, and support portions of previous control-satisfaction investigations.
