TY  - JOUR
T1  - Local-Cosmopolitan Orientations and Career Strategies for Specialists
AU  - Delbecq, Andre' L.
AU  - Elfner, Eliot S.
Y1  - 1970/12/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254828
DO  - 10.5465/254828
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 373
EP  - 387
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The research reported sought to operationalize the Thompson, Avery, and Carlson model for career strategies, and to relate these strategies to occupational orientation toward either the employing organization (local) or the speciality (cosmopolitan). The resulting modified conceptualization was tested using a sample of veterinarian scientists employed by a government agency. Results indicated that the operationalization of the modified Thompson model was successful. Further, scientists choosing a stable career strategy seemed to have a low occupational orientation relative to their speciality. However, scientists choosing an organizational strategy seemed to be both oriented toward their speciality and their organization.
AB  - The research reported sought to operationalize the Thompson, Avery, and Carlson model for career strategies, and to relate these strategies to occupational orientation toward either the employing organization (local) or the speciality (cosmopolitan). The resulting modified conceptualization was tested using a sample of veterinarian scientists employed by a government agency. Results indicated that the operationalization of the modified Thompson model was successful. Further, scientists choosing a stable career strategy seemed to have a low occupational orientation relative to their speciality. However, scientists choosing an organizational strategy seemed to be both oriented toward their speciality and their organization.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/254828
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/254828
Y2  - 2026/04/24
