JO  - AMJ
SP  - 439
EP  - 448
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article reports on the format and structure of introductory courses in industrial management. The author suggests that introductory management courses should be restructured to account for developments within the industry. It is further proposed that relevant business textbooks be integrated into the business curriculum. Textbooks related to subjects including quantitative research techniques, industrial organization, organizational behavior, and system analysis are recommended. The book ?Introduction to Behavioral Science for Business,? by Blair J Kolasa is also discussed.
