TY  - JOUR
T1  - Human Relations Training for Middle Management: A Field Experiment
AU  - Hand, Herbert H.
AU  - Slocum, John W.
Y1  - 1970/12/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254830
DO  - 10.5465/254830
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 403
EP  - 410
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A field experiment was conducted in a specialty steel plant that was attempting to improve human relations practices. The research design included the use of an experimental and a control group and pre training, post training, and post-post training measurements. The independent variables were 1) the effect of the 28-week training program, and 2) the longitudinal effect of training. Dependent variables were knowledge, attitudes, and behavior. The statistical results indicated that the training was ineffective.
AB  - A field experiment was conducted in a specialty steel plant that was attempting to improve human relations practices. The research design included the use of an experimental and a control group and pre training, post training, and post-post training measurements. The independent variables were 1) the effect of the 28-week training program, and 2) the longitudinal effect of training. Dependent variables were knowledge, attitudes, and behavior. The statistical results indicated that the training was ineffective.
