T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 389
EP  - 401
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Rational decision-making is essential for the long-term success of any organization. For lower-level managers, much of their experience in decision-making is derived from recurrent decision problems. This study analyzes the decision patterns of three lower managerial levels and then contrasts these data with the optimal results generated by a dynamic programming model.
